Source: binutils
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Tux Mason <tuxmason@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), bison
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: https://www.gnu.org/software/binutils

Package: libbfd
Section: libdevel
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: libc (>= 1.1.8), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: The Binary File Descriptor library
 This package provides libbfd, a shared library which 
 contains binary file descriptor routines.

Package: libopcodes
Section: libdevel
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: libc (>= 1.1.8), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: provides routines for dealing with opcodes
 A library for dealing with opcodes - the "readable text" 
 versions of instructions for the processor.

Package: binutils-dev
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: libz-dev (>= 1.1.8), bison, libbfd (= ${binary:Version}), libopcodes (= ${binary:Version})
Description: static libraries and development headers
 This package provides static versions of the libraries 
 libbfd and libopcodes. Also included are header files
 required for developement using binutils.

Package: binutils
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: binutils-dev (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends} 
Description: a collection of binary tools
 contains a linker, an assembler, and other tools for handling 
 object files.

Package: binutils-doc
Section: doc
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Recommends: man-db, info
Depends: binutils (= ${binary:Version})
Description: documentation for binutils
 This package provides info and manpages for binutils
